headline: Nuclear Stocks Weren't Immune To AI-Led Stock Market Retreat But Then Powell Spoke
summary: Nuclear-related stocks, which have roared higher over the past twelve months amid AI-data center growth expectations, turned positive Friday following Federal Reserve Chairman Jerome Powell signaling that the door is wide open for a rate cut next month.  Heading into Friday's stock market, nuclear stocks angled lower on the week as the broader AI-dominated stock market paused to consolidate.  S&P 500 nuclear giants Constellation Energy and Vistra entered Friday's stock market down 3% and 3.6%, respectively, for the week.
